-- Persian Gulf Shares: Arabtec, Dar Al Arkan, Kuwait Finance House
-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 2012-05-23T12:06:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-23/persian-gulf-shares-arabtec-dar-al-arkan-kuwait-finance-house.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  fell 1.1
percent, the most since May 16, to 1,480.10 at the 2 p.m. close
in the emirate. Kuwait’s measure slid 0.2 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Arabtec Holding Co. (ARTC)   declined as much as 2.1
percent to 2.86 dirhams before trimming losses to 2.9 dirhams.
The biggest publicly traded construction company in the United
Arab Emirates was lowered to sell from hold at Deutsche Bank AG.  Dar Al Arkan Real Estate Development Co. (ALARKAN)  
climbed as much as 2.3 percent to 11.30 riyals before trading at
11.15 riyals. The Saudi company sold land to  Saudi Basic
Industries Corp. (SABIC)   for 742 million riyals ($198
million). Sabic declined 0.3 percent.  Kuwait Finance House (KFIN)   climbed for a third day,
gaining 2.8 percent to 730 fils after the Kuwaiti Islamic lender
said it’s in talks to sell a stake in Al Salam Hospital Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
